interaction:
  user_prompt: Mode 2 explanation and clarifying Q&A
  assistant_response_summary: "Fully defined Mode 2: same movement/claiming rules as Mode 1. When a player is trapped, opponent continues if they have valid moves. Game ends when both are trapped or board is full. Winner = largest 4-connected island (flood fill). Tiebreakers: 1) largest island size, 2) total squares claimed, 3) whoever got trapped first loses. Isthmus-connected regions count as one island."
